Pychem 0.1.2 Readme

LICENSE
-------

PyChem is distributed under the GNU GPL license.
For details read the file COPYING.

DOCUMENTATION and SUPPORT
-------------------------

If you have problems with using or installing PyChem, consult
the online documentation and support at http://molmod.UGent.be/code/pychem/

Most of the source code is self-documented. For example the documentation
about pychem.moldata can be read using the python interpreter with the following
two commands:
>>> import pychem.moldata
>>> help(pychem.moldata)

INSTALLING
----------

PyChem depends on:
    - python 2.4
    - Numeric
    
To install Pychem on your system, run this command:
$ python setup.py install

